getSubject

public ISysSubject getSubject()
Description copied from interface: ISysBusEvent
Get the ISysSubject on which the message was received. This is useful if you added a wildchar-listener or the same listener on different subjects (second is not recomended).

getReplySubject

public ISysSubject getReplySubject()
Description copied from interface: ISysBusEvent
Get the ISysSubject on which the requester is listening. This is useful to check, wether this message was sent as a request. The method should not be used to publish messages on this subject afterwards.

Specified by:
getReplySubject in interface ISysBusEvent
Returns:
a ISysSubject object, null if the event is originating from a broadcast message and does not have a reply-subject.
